    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p>In Act 2, the draugr thrall appears in a more advanced form — recently turned through the Wyrd-Draugr's binding magic rather than ancient barrow-rites. These thralls are smaller and weaker than their barrow-bound counterparts, their decay more recent and less complete, driven by a newer and rawer hunger. The Wyrd-Draugr's Organized Undead feature grants them advantage on initiative and their opening attacks, making even these fragile minions briefly dangerous.</p>",
